1
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:12,633
<i>Does Jessica visit you
in your dreams, too?</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,900
<i>Did she tell you her last wish?</i>

3
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:16,033
<i> Her last wish?</i>

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,467
<i>She said she wants us
to get back together.</i>

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,100
<i> She would never say that!</i>

6
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:21,100
<i>- Ma'am Felma, watch this.
- What is it, Didang?</i>

7
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,667
<i> This is not confirmed, okay?</i>

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,567
<i>Looks like this girl,
might be behind bars soon,</i>

9
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,167
<i> who allegedly pushed</i>

10
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,267
<i>the hit-and-run victim,
Jessica Capistrano Cruz.</i>

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,667
<i> I'm going to jail.</i>

12
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:32,900
<i>- Coleen!
- I'm going to jail!</i>

13
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,733
<i>So it wasn't true that her last
wish was for you and Manuel</i>

14
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:37,367
<i> to get back together?</i>

15
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,233
<i> Of course not.</i>

16
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:42,267
<i>But I know Manuel
will come around.</i>

17
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,067
<i> Jeff, Andeng.</i>

18
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,333
<i>Forgive me, but I have
to leave you again.</i>

19
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:49,333
<i>I need to do this
to save Coleen.</i>

20
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:50,733
<i>What do you mean
by leave, Manuel?</i>

21
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:57,733
Manuel, no!

22
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,900
You're not going back
to that woman.

23
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,333
Can't you see?

24
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:06,867
She planned all of this.

25
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,400
She paid Timo to lie.

26
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:19,633
And now she's the one
who'll fix it?

27
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,867
She'll be the one to make Timo
withdraw his statement?

28
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:27,400
What a load of crap.

29
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:30,867
We're the ones who should file
a case against her.

30
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:34,200
Perjury and bribery!

31
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:37,133
Felma, we have no proof!

32
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,833
We'll find one, Manuel!

33
00:01:39,867 --> 00:01:42,833
Where? How? And when?

34
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:45,333
Remember, Felma.

35
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,833
Coleen's freedom
is what we're after.

36
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:49,100
We have to move

37
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,200
before the court hands down
a decision.

38
00:01:54,067 --> 00:01:55,633
Manuel!

39
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,100
You're going to leave
our children again!

40
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:02,667
They'll get mad at you again!

41
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,933
Felma, I'll just accept it
if they get angry.

42
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,567
I'd rather be away
from Jeffrey and Andrea

43
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,133
than see Coleen in jail.

44
00:02:10,067 --> 00:02:11,633
Felma...

45
00:02:11,767 --> 00:02:13,867
This is so hard for me.

46
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,633
But what can I do?

47
00:02:17,033 --> 00:02:18,067
This is the only way

48
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,800
to prevent Coleen
from getting locked up.

49
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:22,900
I also don't want Coleen
to go to jail.

50
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:26,567
But are we just going to let
that happen?

51
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,300
To let that woman win?

52
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:35,400
Will you let her manipulate you?

53
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:45,300
It's ridiculously stupid to let
that woman get the upper hand!

54
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,200
Felma, fine!
Call it complete stupidity!

55
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,133
But if it means Coleen
gets her freedom...

56
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:54,033
then fine,
I'll return to Hazel.

57
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,367
No, Manuel.

58
00:03:00,367 --> 00:03:01,800
No.

59
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,200
There's still another way.

60
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:08,533
What is it?

61
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:18,467
<i> Hello, Manuel.</i>

62
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,133
Have you already thought
about the help

63
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,933
I'm offering for Coleen?

64
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,133
Help?

65
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:30,200
That's not help, Hazel.

66
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:32,833
That's a trap.

67
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:35,367
You only want
to get Manuel back.

68
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,467
<i> Oh, hello, Felma.</i>

69
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,700
Why's your temper flaring up
so quickly?

70
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:42,333
You can never get Manuel back.

71
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:44,400
<i> Never again.</i>

72
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,067
Because this time...

73
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:53,600
I'm keeping the man
I love all to myself!

74
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:54,800
<i> Wow.</i>

75
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:56,767
<i> Intense.</i>

76
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:59,600
The way you said it hits hard.

77
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:01,800
<i> So that means...</i>

78
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:02,867
it's fine with you

79
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,500
if your dearest youngest
ends up in jail,

80
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:07,700
just so you can hoard Manuel?

81
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,467
How selfish.

82
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:14,667
Do you really think I'll let
my daughter go to jail?

83
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,900
I hate playing dirty.

84
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,800
But you're pushing me
to do that.

85
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:25,800
Fine.

86
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:27,500
<i> Let's play dirty.</i>

87
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,933
Are you serious?

88
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:33,300
<i> Is that you, Felma?</i>

89
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:35,033
That's new.

90
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:37,400
It's so not you.

91
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:39,000
Go ahead, Felma.

92
00:04:39,133 --> 00:04:40,700
What will you do then?

93
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:46,300
I'll use my money to get
what I want.

94
00:04:47,133 --> 00:04:48,233
<i> Yes, Hazel.</i>

95
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:51,733
I have more money than you.

96
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:56,200
If you can pay,
I can pay even more!

97
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:00,367
Hello?

98
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,167
What? Felma, are you going
to bribe Timo?

99
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:13,133
Earlier, you said to Noah
you won't do what Hazel did.

100
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:14,667
We have no other choice.

101
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,800
I don't want Coleen
to go to jail.

102
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:21,400
But I don't want you
to go back to Hazel.

103
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:24,767
Sure, our child
might get freed...

104
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,867
but you'll be...

105
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:32,100
the one chained to that woman.

106
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,933
I don't want that, Manuel.

107
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:39,533
I won't let that happen.

108
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,067
I won't let that happen.

109
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:47,233
And we won't be paying Timo.

110
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,667
We'll pay his wife.

111
00:05:59,533 --> 00:06:00,933
That's three hundred
thousand pesos.

112
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:05,400
That's all for you.

113
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:10,500
So that you and your children
can have a better life.

114
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,600
Just please help us.

115
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:17,400
Can you please talk to Timo?

116
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,200
Convince him to retract
his statement

117
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,400
against Coleen?

118
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:45,100
I'm sorry,
but I can't accept this.

119
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:50,167
Is this not enough?

120
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:52,233
We'll give you more.

121
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:56,333
Ma'am, we're not giving up
our principles for anything.

122
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:04,967
I'm sorry.

123
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,667
I'm sorry if you feel insulted.

124
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,900
We hate doing this.

125
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:13,800
We don't want to pay

126
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,733
but we're out of options.

127
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,700
We need your help.

128
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,100
And Hazel said...

129
00:07:19,233 --> 00:07:21,967
Please leave!
We have nothing to talk about.

130
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:26,900
<i>- Diana.
- Leave! Get lost!</i>

131
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:14,533
What does Hazel have
on that woman...

132
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:17,700
that made her turn down
our offer?

133
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:21,067
I can't also make sense
of that wicked Hazel.

134
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,533
Thank you.

135
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,100
You know what?

136
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:34,800
While you were talking
to Felma and Manuel...

137
00:08:35,967 --> 00:08:38,700
I was also talking
to my henchman, Maximo.

138
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:40,867
He was waiting.

139
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:45,867
The inmates were also waiting
to make Timo's life hell inside.

140
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:50,033
Good thing you didn't give in
to their offer.

141
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:55,167
You've lost a lot of money.

142
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:57,700
But just think
about it instead...

143
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,967
what's the use
of all that money

144
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:04,633
if your husband
suffers every day?

145
00:09:08,967 --> 00:09:10,400
Oh please! Can you not?

146
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:12,267
Cut the drama.

147
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,500
Don't worry.

148
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:18,267
You and your kids will still
receive monthly support from me.

149
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,733
So stop being dramatic.

150
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,100
Manuel, does this mean...

151
00:09:31,567 --> 00:09:33,267
Manuel.

152
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:39,567
Manuel, I don't want you
to go back to Hazel.

153
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,200
I don't want that either, Felma.

154
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,600
I don't, I really don't.

155
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:45,800
But we don't have
any other choice.

156
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:48,767
This is the only way
to set Coleen free.

157
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:53,233
And I realized, Felma...

158
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,533
I still have a responsibility
to Hazel.

159
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,433
She's still my wife.

160
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:59,667
And we lost our child.

161
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,800
I'm the only one she has left.

162
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:03,800
She needs me.

163
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,367
I understand.

164
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:14,900
But we have to discuss this...

165
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:16,967
with the kids.

166
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,733
No, don't, Felma.

167
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:20,700
They should know...

168
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,267
so they understand.

169
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:24,833
If not...

170
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,600
they'll get mad at you again.

171
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:31,533
If Coleen finds out,

172
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,633
she might blame herself.

173
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,933
I don't want her to know
she's the reason

174
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:39,200
why I have to be with Hazel.

175
00:10:39,967 --> 00:10:41,400
She will carry that burden.

176
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,800
You know what, Felma?

177
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:47,900
It's okay if they get mad at me.

178
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:48,900
I'll be fine with it.

179
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:50,833
What matters is that
you're together.

180
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:53,033
You're together like before.

181
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:58,000
I'm the only reason why
this is all happening.

182
00:10:58,133 --> 00:10:59,100
You were doing fine before.

183
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,633
But everything got messed up
when I came back.

184
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:03,333
That's why it's better...

185
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:05,933
Felma, please.

186
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,933
I will leave,
so the peace can return.

187
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,600
But you'll suffer
for the rest of your life

188
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:17,233
living with that woman.

189
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:22,133
It's just a little sacrifice
for Coleen's freedom and future.

190
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,867
It won't come true again...

191
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:35,833
my dream of rebuilding
our family.

192
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:41,767
Felma, maybe we don't need
to be living together

193
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:43,900
to say our family is whole.

194
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:48,700
Felma, It's enough as long
as we love each other.

195
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:54,133
It's so hard
to love you, Manuel.

196
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,000
You're elusive.

197
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,933
I can't claim you.

198
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,800
I can't have you.

199
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:06,333
Because Hazel's always
trying to take you.

200
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,200
It's so unfair.

201
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:12,033
It's so unfair.

202
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:16,500
I have to teach myself again
not to love you.

203
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:17,800
Felma, don't.

204
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,700
Don't be like that, Felma.

205
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,700
Don't try to learn
how not to love me.

206
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,300
Please, I'm begging you.

207
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:26,167
Please keep loving me, Felma.

208
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:29,400
Keep loving me.

209
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:33,100
Keep loving me.

210
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:36,667
Keep loving me, Felma.

211
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,633
Have mercy, please.

212
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:42,633
Have mercy, please.

213
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,633
Manuel?

214
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,567
Manuel?

215
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:10,600
Does it mean...

216
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:13,367
you've already
made a decision?

217
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:16,433
This is only to fulfill
Jessica's wish.

218
00:13:16,567 --> 00:13:18,133
And for Coleen's case.

219
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:21,700
Make sure Timo
will retract his statement.

220
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:24,800
Of course.

221
00:13:25,667 --> 00:13:26,900
Consider it done.

222
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:37,867
Manuel, what about your stuff?

223
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:39,567
Didn't you bring anything?

224
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,300
<i> Manuel, I'll take you there.</i>

225
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,933
<i> You don't have to, Felma.</i>

226
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:50,067
<i>I booked a ride
in "Sakay Extra" for PWD.</i>

227
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:54,867
<i>And I don't want you and Hazel
to see each other.</i>

228
00:13:58,633 --> 00:14:00,767
Aren't you coming home yet?

229
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:01,967
Not yet.

230
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:04,100
When?

231
00:14:04,233 --> 00:14:05,900
Once Coleen's case is fixed.

232
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:09,833
After Timo retracts
his statement.

233
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:14,167
Manuel, I need an assurance.

234
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,600
Come home first.

235
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:21,767
No, do what we agreed on first.

236
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:24,267
Don't you trust me?

237
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,500
I don't.

238
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,667
I'm sorry...

239
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,667
but my condition is...

240
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,633
you have to come home
first, Manuel.

241
00:14:36,367 --> 00:14:38,833
Take it or leave it.

242
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,500
The nerve of Hazel
to ask for assurance!

243
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:53,333
So shameless!

244
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:58,533
What if she doesn't keep her
side of the bargain?

245
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:02,167
She'll fool you again.

246
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,467
Us.

247
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:06,833
It's hard to trust
someone like her.

248
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,567
She fooled us
so many times, Manuel!

249
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:13,400
I won't let her do that again.

250
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:15,900
If that happens,
you won't even have to hurt her.

251
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:18,467
I might end up
killing her myself.

252
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,767
We're not like this.

253
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,167
We don't think ill of others.

254
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,700
But because Hazel is evil,

255
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:29,367
we forget to be good people.

256
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,967
Sorry, Felma.

257
00:15:33,367 --> 00:15:35,833
<i>- Enough, enough!
- Oh, just a little bit.</i>

258
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:42,067
<i>Are you okay?
Oh, you're still okay, right?</i>

259
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,700
<i> This is all my fault.</i>

260
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:51,167
<i>Because I let myself be weak
for a night.</i>

261
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,600
That's where it all started.

262
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:56,733
Right there.

263
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,167
Because I was stupid!

264
00:16:01,633 --> 00:16:06,467
That Hazel deliberately forced
herself into our lives.

265
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,733
She seduced you.

266
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:09,400
She trapped you into marriage.

267
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:12,100
Yes, but I still
let myself be weak.

268
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:14,967
It's on me, Felma.

269
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:18,967
I need to do this,

270
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,200
so she'll stay away
from all of you.

271
00:16:28,233 --> 00:16:29,767
It already happened.

272
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:32,800
Manuel?

273
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,067
Manuel, can you do me a favor?

274
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:39,867
Let's ask for another day.

275
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,033
So we can spend time
together as a family,

276
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:46,800
even for a day and be happy.

277
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:52,400
I knew it, they're here.

278
00:16:56,700 --> 00:17:01,300
Mom? Why are you packing
dad's stuff?

279
00:17:11,133 --> 00:17:12,367
Take it or leave it?

280
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,733
Why did you have to play
hard to get?

281
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,167
I don't trust Manuel.

282
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:21,400
And even more so
with Flirty Felma.

283
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:23,967
What does Felma
have to do with it?

284
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,967
Manuel made that decision.

285
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:30,000
If I make Timo retract
his statement now,

286
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:34,633
later on, Felma could push
Manuel not to return to me.

287
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:35,800
No way.

288
00:17:35,933 --> 00:17:37,733
They can't outsmart me.

289
00:17:37,867 --> 00:17:40,167
Manuel has to come back
to me first

290
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,733
before I make a move.

291
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:44,567
Okay.

292
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,900
Your mom and I decided...

293
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:53,667
that we're going on a trip.

294
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:58,133
What?

295
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:03,800
Isn't it awkward and off

296
00:18:03,933 --> 00:18:07,433
if we take a vacation
in the middle of Coleen's trial?

297
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:08,567
Dear...

298
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:10,200
We need a breather.

299
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,800
And I talked to Attorney Yeban.

300
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,667
I'm not leading you on,

301
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:22,933
but it seems the case might
swing in Coleen's favor.

302
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,233
What is that?

303
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:26,533
Did you hear that, sweetie?

304
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:30,667
Our canceled vacation to Laguna
is finally happening.

305
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,933
What will happen
to the case, Mom?

306
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:36,600
Did the lawyer give you details?

307
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:38,633
He hasn't, dear, but...

308
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:41,067
I'll make sure we'll win.

309
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,800
You won't go to jail, sweetie.

310
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:44,133
I promise you that.

311
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:48,533
What are you waiting for?

312
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:50,933
Pack your bags for our trip.

313
00:18:51,067 --> 00:18:53,767
Trip? When? Where?

314
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,967
Ma'am, Sir,
can I also pack my bag?

315
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:00,467
Of course, Didang.

316
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,967
You're coming with us.

317
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,900
But wait,
don't forget the...

318
00:19:04,033 --> 00:19:05,567
Yes, Ma'am,
I won't forget anything.

319
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:07,267
I will remember everything.

320
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,267
Yes, Ma'am.

321
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,500
Ma'am, I'm going to start
packing now.

322
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:11,933
Sir!

323
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,767
Let's go
while she's still packing.

324
00:19:31,667 --> 00:19:32,767
Yes!

325
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:36,533
Yes! Finally, I'm out!

326
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:39,133
We bought a padlock
for the house,

327
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,467
so we can leave anytime!

328
00:19:41,867 --> 00:19:43,200
Andrea, let's take
a picture first.

329
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:44,533
<i>- Didang.
- Ma'am.</i>

330
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:46,167
<i> Grab our stuff, come on.</i>

331
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:48,033
- I'm on it.
- Excited?

332
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:51,367
Son, make sure we don't
forget anything.

333
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,067
Yes, Mom, I got this.

334
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,367
Thanks, Didang.

335
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:56,833
- Right?
- Yes, she's excited.

336
00:19:56,967 --> 00:19:58,467
She's finally out.

337
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,900
Come on.

338
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,633
There, is it complete now?

339
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,433
Auntie Felma,
Uncle Manuel.

340
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:21,733
Joel, why are you here?

341
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:24,000
- I didn't...
- I invited him.

342
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:26,400
Because when you're sad,

343
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:27,933
and you need Joel,
he's right there.

344
00:20:28,067 --> 00:20:30,000
But when you're happy,
you forget about him.

345
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:31,633
What are you, a user?

346
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:33,200
- User already?
- Yes.

347
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:38,400
Sorry, Joel, I thought
it was just family.

348
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,400
Why? A brother-in-law is part
of the family.

349
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:41,500
Right, brother-in-law?

350
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:42,733
Family! Brother-in-law.

351
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,767
- Stop it, Jeffrey.
- Enough, both of you.

352
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:48,167
Come on, your godparents
are waiting inside.

353
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:49,800
- Let's go.
- They're here, too?

354
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,633
Of course, we invited them.

355
00:20:51,767 --> 00:20:53,867
Even Noah.

356
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,333
Sir Manuel, are you sure?

357
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,633
You invited a rival?

358
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:01,567
Didang, no rivals here.

359
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:03,000
Of course,

360
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:05,900
He's one of the people
who helped Coleen, or us.

361
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:07,833
He should be here.

362
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,467
So, I guess I'll be waiting
for a boxing match.

363
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:15,433
And of course, my Ma'am Felma
is the round girl.

364
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:18,833
The prize is her heart that
flutters all over the place.

365
00:21:18,967 --> 00:21:21,700
Didang, stop it.

366
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:24,667
Noah won't be coming.

367
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,667
He has something to take care
of in Davao.

368
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:31,500
Oh! Knockout already!

369
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:35,667
Didang, there's no boxing match
for mom's heart.

370
00:21:36,233 --> 00:21:37,267
Dad's already won.

371
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:40,400
There!

372
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,400
We love Uncle Noah, too,

373
00:21:43,567 --> 00:21:45,300
but of course, Team Dad!

374
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:47,700
- FelManuel forever!
- You talk too much.

375
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:48,833
That pickup line
didn't sound good.

376
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:50,400
Come on, let's go inside.

377
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:51,900
- You know...
- We're wasting time.

378
00:21:52,033 --> 00:21:53,867
You're annoying.
Let's go, Dad.

379
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:59,067
Yes, I'll support you
even if your dad jokes are ugly.

380
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,267
- Good morning.
- Thank you.

381
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:12,067
Thank you.

382
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:20,567
Hola!<i> Mabuhay</i> !

383
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:23,000
Welcome to Matawhay
Garden Resort!

384
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,500
Such a lovely place.

385
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:26,900
Where you can rest in peace.

386
00:22:28,033 --> 00:22:29,800
Rest in peace.

387
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:33,100
- Two deluxe rooms, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

388
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:35,333
- And one couple's room.
- Thank you.

389
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:37,100
- Couple's room?
- Couple's room?

390
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:41,067
For Abel and Paz.

391
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,467
And for the girls,
the deluxe room.

392
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,400
And the boys
get the other deluxe room.

393
00:22:45,533 --> 00:22:49,033
Good, just to be clear.

394
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,767
I thought...

395
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,300
- Calm down.
- No!

396
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:55,200
Because they're not allowed
to share a room.

397
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:56,200
That's it.

398
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:58,633
We're just here to enjoy, okay?

399
00:22:58,767 --> 00:23:01,000
Your mom and I want us...

400
00:23:01,133 --> 00:23:02,833
all to be happy.

401
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:05,667
No one mentions
any problems, all right?

402
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,800
And no phones for now.

403
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:09,767
- We'll be watching you.
- Why?

404
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:13,600
It's been so long since
we were together like this.

405
00:23:13,733 --> 00:23:17,600
So I want us to focus
on each other.

406
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:19,233
No distractions.

407
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:24,333
So we can make
lots of happy memories

408
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:25,867
while I'm still here.

409
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,600
Dad...

410
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,767
<i>Looks like you're about
to cry, Andeng.</i>

411
00:23:41,167 --> 00:23:43,767
I can't reach Felma and Manuel.

412
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,400
That's what you get
for acting hard to get.

413
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:49,367
Alice, what if they ran away
from me?

414
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:50,900
Why is Hazel calling?

415
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:52,867
Abel, is Manuel with you?

416
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,667
Hey! Sorry, girl.

417
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,267
Do not disturb.

418
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:58,967
He's with his real family.

419
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:01,200
We're joining
their family bonding.

420
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:02,500
I'm the real wife.

421
00:24:02,633 --> 00:24:03,533
I should be there.

422
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:06,200
No illegitimate family
is going to enjoy today.

423
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:08,433
Because I'm going
to ruin their day.
